16
00:01:57,875 --> 00:02:01,000
<i>- Are you going to forget?</i>

17
00:02:01,083 --> 00:02:03,583
- Hey, Kousei.
you feel sick or something?

18
00:02:03,666 --> 00:02:04,750
- I'm fine.

19
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:07,041
- Well, you look pretty
wrecked.

20
00:02:07,125 --> 00:02:08,541
I'm just saying.

21
00:02:11,250 --> 00:02:14,458
How about we go pay Kaori
a visit later on?

22
00:02:14,541 --> 00:02:17,375
I bet she'd love to see us
all together like that.

23
00:02:17,458 --> 00:02:19,041
Let's do it.
It'll be fun.

24
00:02:19,125 --> 00:02:20,791
- Yeah, good call!

25
00:02:20,875 --> 00:02:22,625
- Maybe next time,
all right?

26
00:02:22,708 --> 00:02:27,000
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

27
00:02:27,083 --> 00:02:28,833
- You think he
and Kaori

28
00:02:28,916 --> 00:02:30,125
got into a fight, maybe?

29
00:02:30,208 --> 00:02:32,000
♪♪

30
00:02:32,083 --> 00:02:34,791
- Who knows,
and so what if they did?

31
00:02:34,875 --> 00:02:36,166
- Because they're friends.

32
00:02:36,250 --> 00:02:37,208
- Yeah, they're friends,

33
00:02:37,291 --> 00:02:37,916
but she's also the competition.

34
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:40,958
- We're not competing.

35
00:02:41,041 --> 00:02:43,333
If he's all bummed out about
some music thing,

36
00:02:43,416 --> 00:02:45,458
it's not like I can help
him out with it.

37
00:02:45,541 --> 00:02:46,625
He's down in the dumps.

38
00:02:46,708 --> 00:02:50,625
Taking him to see Kaori
seems like a no-brainer.

39
00:02:50,708 --> 00:02:54,125
- Just make sure you're
not sabotaging yourself, okay?

40
00:02:54,208 --> 00:02:55,333
You've been studying for that

41
00:02:55,416 --> 00:02:57,750
high school entrance exam
like crazy.

42
00:02:57,833 --> 00:02:59,291
You chose a school that's
way out of your league,

43
00:02:59,375 --> 00:03:02,541
all because it's close
to that music prep campus

44
00:03:02,625 --> 00:03:04,708
Kousei's been looking at.

45
00:03:04,791 --> 00:03:06,833
- It's obvious.
- [grunts]

46
00:03:06,916 --> 00:03:09,166
[sighs]

47
00:03:09,250 --> 00:03:11,500
♪♪

48
00:03:11,583 --> 00:03:14,041
- Well, it's just that Kousei's
so helpless on his own,

49
00:03:14,125 --> 00:03:15,416
I have to go with him.

50
00:03:15,500 --> 00:03:17,291
- You could just be honest
with him, you know.

51
00:03:17,375 --> 00:03:18,083
It'd be a lot easier.

52
00:03:21,916 --> 00:03:26,166
- The truth is,
I wish he'd go someplace local.

53
00:03:26,250 --> 00:03:29,416
Thinking about it,
I get nervous,

54
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:31,208
and I get kinda mad at him.

55
00:03:31,291 --> 00:03:33,958
<i>- When he said to go</i>
<i>without him,</i>

56
00:03:34,041 --> 00:03:35,958
<i>I felt so relieved,</i>

57
00:03:36,041 --> 00:03:39,041
<i>and so guilty, too.</i>

58
00:03:39,125 --> 00:03:41,625
'Course, I don't want Kousei
to see me like that,

59
00:03:41,708 --> 00:03:44,250
so I gotta keep up
my game face.

60
00:03:45,291 --> 00:03:48,583
Maybe I'm just a horrible
person on the inside.

61
00:03:48,666 --> 00:03:53,041
♪♪

62
00:03:53,125 --> 00:03:55,041
<i>I'm finding all</i>
<i>these sides of myself</i>

63
00:03:55,125 --> 00:03:57,875
<i>I didn't know,</i>
<i>and once I've seen them,</i>

64
00:03:57,958 --> 00:03:59,208
<i>I have to deal with them.</i>

65
00:03:59,291 --> 00:04:03,916
<i>I guess that's just part</i>
<i>of being in love.</i>

66
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:05,208
[smacking]

67
00:04:05,291 --> 00:04:06,500
- [sighs]

68
00:04:06,583 --> 00:04:07,583
I don't know where your head
is at, Kousei,

69
00:04:07,666 --> 00:04:10,541
but it sure ain't here.
call it a day.

70
00:04:10,625 --> 00:04:11,250
- [grunts]

71
00:04:11,333 --> 00:04:13,375
- Yeah, you're right.

72
00:04:13,458 --> 00:04:15,416
[door opens]

73
00:04:18,333 --> 00:04:19,416
- Ah, I have to leave,
Ms. Seto!

74
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:21,750
I forgot there's something
I need to do!

75
00:04:21,833 --> 00:04:23,250
- Uh, yeah.

76
00:04:23,333 --> 00:04:25,000
Try to cheer him up,
would you?

77
00:04:31,250 --> 00:04:32,791
- [grunts]

78
00:04:32,875 --> 00:04:35,916
- Hey, wait up, Arima!

79
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:38,250
[breathing heavily]

80
00:04:38,333 --> 00:04:40,291
You're way taller than me
but I was still able

81
00:04:40,375 --> 00:04:42,750
to catch up
to you pretty easily.

82
00:04:42,833 --> 00:04:44,250
You know why that is?

83
00:04:44,333 --> 00:04:45,625
It's 'cause you're slouching!

84
00:04:45,708 --> 00:04:48,916
How else could my tiny legs
catch up to you?

85
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:50,875
So he looks at me and says,

86
00:04:50,958 --> 00:04:52,958
"When I play my oboe
at the festival,

87
00:04:53,041 --> 00:04:54,875
know it's for you, Nagi."

88
00:04:54,958 --> 00:04:56,750
He meant for it to sound cool.

89
00:04:56,833 --> 00:04:58,458
Like I would be impressed
by that.

90
00:04:58,541 --> 00:05:01,750
- Honestly, so that wouldn't
impress you even a tiny bit?

91
00:05:01,833 --> 00:05:04,583
- Only if the guy's cute.

92
00:05:04,666 --> 00:05:05,291
- [chuckles]
- [grunts]

93
00:05:05,375 --> 00:05:07,750
- And I'm guessing he's not.

94
00:05:07,833 --> 00:05:09,458
- I finally made you laugh!
- [grunts]

95
00:05:09,541 --> 00:05:11,083
- [chuckles]

96
00:05:13,416 --> 00:05:14,333
- Thanks for that, Nagi.

97
00:05:14,416 --> 00:05:16,791
I hope I didn't worry you guys
too much.

98
00:05:16,875 --> 00:05:17,958
- Who, me?
Worry about you?

99
00:05:18,041 --> 00:05:19,166
That's ridiculous!

100
00:05:19,250 --> 00:05:21,125
I was just telling
a dumb story!

101
00:05:21,208 --> 00:05:23,125
<i>Having a depressed enemy</i>
<i>is boring, that's all.</i>

102
00:05:23,208 --> 00:05:26,541
<i>- This Arima guy</i>
<i>is unbelievable!</i>

103
00:05:26,625 --> 00:05:27,958
<i>Everyone's freaking out</i>

104
00:05:28,041 --> 00:05:29,291
<i>'cause he's got</i>
<i>the whole song memorized</i>

105
00:05:29,375 --> 00:05:31,458
<i>and he acts like it's</i>
<i>no big deal.</i>

106
00:05:31,541 --> 00:05:33,708
<i>He was like the sheriff</i>
<i>in some western,</i>

107
00:05:33,791 --> 00:05:37,166
<i>or like some giant robot</i>
<i>with a heart of pure steel!</i>

108
00:05:37,250 --> 00:05:39,666
<i>Like a hero,</i>
<i>you know?</i>

109
00:05:39,750 --> 00:05:41,666
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

110
00:05:41,750 --> 00:05:44,333
Damn it!

111
00:05:44,416 --> 00:05:47,625
<i>- What do I say</i>
<i>that won't make it worse?</i>

112
00:05:47,708 --> 00:05:48,708
<i>"Best of luck?</i>

113
00:05:48,791 --> 00:05:51,875
<i>Maybe you'll finally</i>
<i>beat him?"</i>

114
00:05:51,958 --> 00:05:55,541
<i>None of that changes anything.</i>

115
00:05:55,625 --> 00:05:59,375
<i>I'm here because Takeshi needs</i>
<i>to beat you,</i>

116
00:05:59,458 --> 00:06:02,125
<i>and if you're too depressed</i>
<i>to put up a good fight,</i>

117
00:06:02,208 --> 00:06:04,250
<i>the win won't make</i>
<i>things better.</i>

118
00:06:04,333 --> 00:06:06,083
<i>How selfish, right?</i>

119
00:06:06,166 --> 00:06:08,666
<i>I'm an ugly phantom.</i>

120
00:06:08,750 --> 00:06:09,833
- You know what I think?

121
00:06:09,916 --> 00:06:11,208
That oboe is going to be great.

122
00:06:11,291 --> 00:06:13,708
- Huh?
You really think so?

123
00:06:13,791 --> 00:06:15,416
- When you play for the sake
of another person,

124
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:18,958
it can make all the difference
in the world.

125
00:06:19,041 --> 00:06:20,958
<i>- Why do you play piano</i>
<i>in the first place?</i>

126
00:06:21,041 --> 00:06:22,583
<i>Is it for yourself?</i>

127
00:06:22,666 --> 00:06:25,458
- It's like you
and that one friend of yours.

128
00:06:25,541 --> 00:06:27,541
The one you really admire.

129
00:06:27,625 --> 00:06:30,583
You're playing for him,
whether he knows it or not.

130
00:06:30,666 --> 00:06:33,541
- When you've shared your art
with a room full of people,

131
00:06:33,625 --> 00:06:37,791
<i>when you've given them</i>
<i>a window into your soul,</i>

132
00:06:37,875 --> 00:06:39,916
<i>and your hearts beat as one,</i>

133
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:44,208
that's the moment when music
goes deeper than words.

134
00:06:44,291 --> 00:06:47,875
♪♪

135
00:06:47,958 --> 00:06:49,833
- What does that even mean?

136
00:06:49,916 --> 00:06:51,833
If cliches are
the best you've got,

137
00:06:51,916 --> 00:06:54,000
you might as well
save your breath.

138
00:06:56,125 --> 00:06:59,083
[swing squeaking]

139
00:06:59,166 --> 00:07:04,500
♪♪

140
00:07:04,583 --> 00:07:06,333
- [grunts]

141
00:07:06,416 --> 00:07:07,750
<i>Revel.</i>

142
00:07:07,833 --> 00:07:08,750
<i>- Welcome back!</i>

143
00:07:08,833 --> 00:07:10,208
- [grunts]

144
00:07:10,291 --> 00:07:13,500
<i>No, I don't want to hear</i>
<i>"Pavane for a Dead Princess!"</i>

145
00:07:13,583 --> 00:07:15,750
<i>- Wanna kill yourself with me?</i>

146
00:07:15,833 --> 00:07:17,375
<i>- Welcome back.</i>

147
00:07:17,458 --> 00:07:20,416
<i>- Don't make me!</i>
<i>Don't make me think about it!</i>

148
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:24,375
<i>I wish that I couldn't</i>
<i>hear anything.</i>

149
00:07:28,166 --> 00:07:30,750
- What's up?

150
00:07:30,833 --> 00:07:32,333
We're heading over
to the hospital

151
00:07:32,416 --> 00:07:33,083
to go pay Kaori a visit.

152
00:07:33,166 --> 00:07:36,083
Love to have you come with us.

153
00:07:36,166 --> 00:07:37,750
- I don't think so.

154
00:07:37,833 --> 00:07:40,000
- There's no need to hold back
because of us, man.

155
00:07:40,083 --> 00:07:41,375
Come on.

156
00:07:41,458 --> 00:07:43,125
- No, all right?

157
00:07:43,208 --> 00:07:45,625
- What is with you today?

158
00:07:45,708 --> 00:07:47,791
- [grunts]

159
00:07:47,875 --> 00:07:50,458
- Seriously, why are you
giving her the cold shoulder?

160
00:07:50,541 --> 00:07:53,291
After all that Kaori's
done for you,

161
00:07:53,375 --> 00:07:55,833
the minute she gets sick,
you jet?

162
00:07:56,500 --> 00:07:57,541
- [groans]

163
00:07:57,625 --> 00:08:00,041
- [grunts]
You're being a dick!

164
00:08:02,041 --> 00:08:06,416
Hey, man,
are you okay?

165
00:08:06,500 --> 00:08:06,916
- Watari.

166
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:10,375
- [gasps]

167
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:13,875
- What am I supposed to do?

168
00:08:13,958 --> 00:08:17,250
<i>- Honestly,</i>
<i>I'm in pretty bad shape here.</i>

169
00:08:17,333 --> 00:08:19,208
- [gasps]

170
00:08:19,291 --> 00:08:21,500
<i>No, not again.</i>

171
00:08:21,583 --> 00:08:22,708
<i>- I'm sorry.</i>

172
00:08:22,791 --> 00:08:24,583
<i>- I'm making you</i>
<i>remember things</i>

173
00:08:24,666 --> 00:08:26,125
<i>better left forgotten.</i>

174
00:08:26,208 --> 00:08:29,458
<i>You'd be happier</i>
<i>if we had never met, huh?</i>

175
00:08:29,541 --> 00:08:30,625
- [crying]

176
00:08:30,708 --> 00:08:34,166
I just stood there
like an idiot.

177
00:08:34,250 --> 00:08:37,416
I didn't know what to do.

178
00:08:37,500 --> 00:08:39,708
What am I supposed
to do?

179
00:08:39,791 --> 00:08:43,833
[crying]

180
00:08:43,916 --> 00:08:46,833
- Listen, Kousei.

181
00:08:46,916 --> 00:08:49,250
This is just my opinion,

182
00:08:49,333 --> 00:08:51,208
but I really think that
you should go see Kaori

183
00:08:51,291 --> 00:08:54,625
no matter how tough it may be,

184
00:08:54,708 --> 00:08:57,500
'cause if it was me
that she needed right now,

185
00:08:57,583 --> 00:08:59,125
I would do anything.

186
00:08:59,208 --> 00:09:02,416
She could say the word
and I'd drink toilet water.

187
00:09:02,500 --> 00:09:05,000
Just chug it down.

188
00:09:05,083 --> 00:09:06,458
You know what, though?

189
00:09:06,541 --> 00:09:08,250
When it comes to Kaori,

190
00:09:08,333 --> 00:09:12,375
I'm pretty sure that I'm not
the guy she needs right now.

191
00:09:12,458 --> 00:09:14,208
Whenever she stops being
stubborn and wants help,

192
00:09:14,291 --> 00:09:18,041
it isn't me.
It's you.

193
00:09:18,125 --> 00:09:19,583
<i>- Enter a competition.</i>

194
00:09:19,666 --> 00:09:21,458
<i>Be my accompanist!</i>

195
00:09:21,541 --> 00:09:23,375
<i>I want a canele.</i>

196
00:09:23,458 --> 00:09:26,166
<i>You don't know how close</i>
<i>I am right now</i>

197
00:09:26,250 --> 00:09:29,125
<i>to just losing heart!</i>

198
00:09:29,208 --> 00:09:33,333
- But when I see her, Watari,
what do I say?

199
00:09:33,416 --> 00:09:34,625
- Anything.

200
00:09:34,708 --> 00:09:35,666
In the moment,
you'll know what's right.

201
00:09:35,750 --> 00:09:39,416
Sometimes we fellas
gotta wing it.

202
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:42,625
- It feels so impossible.

203
00:09:42,708 --> 00:09:44,583
- Like I told you before,

204
00:09:44,666 --> 00:09:46,083
I think that's up to the girl
to decide.

205
00:09:46,166 --> 00:09:49,916
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

206
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:51,041
♪♪

207
00:09:51,125 --> 00:09:52,916
- I kind of figured
that you'd never come back.

208
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:55,666
- [grunts]

209
00:09:55,750 --> 00:09:56,416
Remember?

210
00:09:56,500 --> 00:09:57,916
I promised you some caneles.

211
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:00,708
- [grunts]

212
00:10:02,125 --> 00:10:04,416
Have you been practicing?

213
00:10:04,500 --> 00:10:05,708
- Yeah.

214
00:10:05,791 --> 00:10:07,375
- How's school?

215
00:10:07,458 --> 00:10:08,083
- Same as always.

216
00:10:08,166 --> 00:10:10,500
- Is everyone good?

217
00:10:10,583 --> 00:10:11,541
- Fine, I guess.

218
00:10:11,625 --> 00:10:13,291
- Those answers all suck!

219
00:10:13,375 --> 00:10:14,666
I bet you don't even wanna
be here in the first place!

220
00:10:14,750 --> 00:10:16,250
- Well, I do!

221
00:10:16,333 --> 00:10:17,791
The truth is,

222
00:10:17,875 --> 00:10:20,541
my answers all suck because
I don't know what to say.

223
00:10:22,625 --> 00:10:25,583
- Then go back to how
your life was before.

224
00:10:25,666 --> 00:10:27,666
All you have to do
is forget about me.

225
00:10:27,750 --> 00:10:29,875
Just press the reset button
in your mind.

226
00:10:29,958 --> 00:10:32,541
One tap and you're done.

227
00:10:32,625 --> 00:10:33,333
<i>- Why?</i>

228
00:10:33,416 --> 00:10:36,625
<i>- I'll never forget.</i>

229
00:10:36,708 --> 00:10:40,125
I'll be gone
and you won't have to be sad.

230
00:10:40,208 --> 00:10:42,166
No point remembering me.

231
00:10:42,250 --> 00:10:45,958
I'm a violinist who can't hold
her own bow anymore.

232
00:10:46,041 --> 00:10:48,708
I'm pretty useless.

233
00:10:48,791 --> 00:10:50,208
<i>- Why?</i>

234
00:10:50,291 --> 00:10:53,041
<i>Why would you say such</i>
<i>a thing?</i>

235
00:10:53,125 --> 00:10:54,625
<i>After all of the yelling</i>
<i>and drama,</i>

236
00:10:54,708 --> 00:10:59,791
<i>after dragging me back onto</i>
<i>that stage,</i>

237
00:10:59,875 --> 00:11:02,166
<i>the memories I've made</i>
<i>with you,</i>

238
00:11:02,250 --> 00:11:04,541
<i>they're precious to me.</i>

239
00:11:04,625 --> 00:11:05,916
[grunts]

240
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:08,500
[angrily chewing]
- No, not the caneles!

241
00:11:08,583 --> 00:11:09,708
<i>- You just told me</i>
<i>to forget you,</i>

242
00:11:09,791 --> 00:11:10,500
<i>so I guess they're mine now,</i>
<i>huh?</i>

243
00:11:10,583 --> 00:11:11,541
<i>- That is a jerk move!</i>

244
00:11:11,625 --> 00:11:13,666
<i>- Well guess</i>
<i>who bought it!</i>

245
00:11:13,750 --> 00:11:15,166
<i>- Shut up!</i>
<i>- You shut up!</i>

246
00:11:15,250 --> 00:11:16,208
<i>- Ooh!</i>
- Not again.

247
00:11:16,291 --> 00:11:18,750
- You're a piece of work.
You know that?

248
00:11:18,833 --> 00:11:21,125
Fine, I'm out of here!

249
00:11:21,208 --> 00:11:21,833
- Wait a sec!

250
00:11:21,916 --> 00:11:24,833
[groans]

251
00:11:24,916 --> 00:11:27,333
[laughing]

252
00:11:27,416 --> 00:11:29,833
<i>You're a weird guy.</i>

253
00:11:29,916 --> 00:11:31,583
<i>You know that, Friend A?</i>

254
00:11:31,666 --> 00:11:35,166
<i>- All of this,</i>
<i>I hate it.</i>

255
00:11:35,250 --> 00:11:37,666
<i>It tears me up inside.</i>

256
00:11:37,750 --> 00:11:40,875
<i>You've given me more</i>
<i>than I could ever repay.</i>

257
00:11:40,958 --> 00:11:42,416
<i>But still,</i>

258
00:11:42,500 --> 00:11:45,500
<i>isn't there anything</i>
<i>I can do for you?</i>

259
00:11:45,583 --> 00:11:49,625
<i>- She could say the word</i>
<i>and I'd drink toilet water.</i>

260
00:11:49,708 --> 00:11:51,750
<i>- It's the reason</i>
<i>I play piano,</i>

261
00:11:51,833 --> 00:11:55,791
<i>because he inspired me.</i>
<i>I want him to know that.</i>

262
00:11:55,875 --> 00:11:58,041
<i>- Look at what I drew!</i>

263
00:11:58,125 --> 00:11:59,875
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

264
00:11:59,958 --> 00:12:02,875
- [gasps]

265
00:12:02,958 --> 00:12:08,416
♪♪

266
00:12:10,208 --> 00:12:11,333
<i>- What?</i>

267
00:12:11,416 --> 00:12:13,750
<i>You wanna play</i>
<i>at my school festival?</i>

268
00:12:13,833 --> 00:12:16,125
<i>This came out of nowhere.</i>
<i>I don't get it.</i>

269
00:12:16,208 --> 00:12:18,208
<i>What the heck is he thinking?</i>

270
00:12:18,291 --> 00:12:21,208
- Don't look at me.
- Please, Nagi!

271
00:12:21,291 --> 00:12:22,625
- I accept.
- [gasps]

272
00:12:22,708 --> 00:12:24,916
- No way!
But this is your time to shine!

273
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:27,125
- Wait, she agreed?
Now what do I do?

274
00:12:27,208 --> 00:12:28,375
I didn't think this far ahead!

275
00:12:28,458 --> 00:12:31,250
<i>- You did this</i>
<i>to yourself, Kousei Arima.</i>

276
00:12:31,333 --> 00:12:33,791
I'm surprised you want to,

277
00:12:33,875 --> 00:12:35,416
but I haven't picked out
a song yet

278
00:12:35,500 --> 00:12:37,750
so this works out pretty well.

279
00:12:37,833 --> 00:12:40,333
- That's a relief.

280
00:12:40,416 --> 00:12:42,208
- [groans]

281
00:12:42,291 --> 00:12:43,333
I gotta ask, though.

282
00:12:43,416 --> 00:12:46,708
What made you wanna do this
in the first place?

283
00:12:46,791 --> 00:12:48,875
[school bells chiming]

284
00:12:48,958 --> 00:12:49,541
[grunts]

285
00:12:49,625 --> 00:12:50,416
[breathing heavily]

286
00:12:50,500 --> 00:12:53,083
- Greetings, my petite princess.

287
00:12:53,166 --> 00:12:56,416
I was hoping we could perhaps
bond over "Der Rosenkavalier."

288
00:12:56,500 --> 00:12:58,708
- I reserved a cozy booth
at the restaurant.

289
00:12:58,791 --> 00:12:59,666
- Hey, Nagi,

290
00:12:59,750 --> 00:13:00,250
you want a crepe
on the way home?

291
00:13:00,333 --> 00:13:02,125
- Rain check!

292
00:13:02,208 --> 00:13:03,041
- Hmm?
- Huh?

293
00:13:03,125 --> 00:13:04,083
- Hot date?

294
00:13:04,166 --> 00:13:06,541
- [humming]

295
00:13:06,625 --> 00:13:08,375
- Try to give it
some more lilt.

296
00:13:08,458 --> 00:13:09,916
It all comes down
to wrist control.

297
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:11,541
- [chomps]

298
00:13:11,625 --> 00:13:13,041
- Maybe you should wait
for an extra beat at the top.

299
00:13:13,125 --> 00:13:16,250
Speeding up the intro
might serve as a nice hook.

300
00:13:16,333 --> 00:13:19,958
- [humming]

301
00:13:20,041 --> 00:13:21,125
<i>No way!</i>

302
00:13:21,208 --> 00:13:22,208
<i>How many times did you run it?</i>

303
00:13:22,291 --> 00:13:24,791
<i>It was great before,</i>
<i>but now...</i>

304
00:13:28,458 --> 00:13:31,416
- Hmm?
Aren't you hungry?

305
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:32,500
- No.

306
00:13:32,583 --> 00:13:34,291
I'm just gonna eat later.

307
00:13:36,750 --> 00:13:38,708
Dibs on the piano.

308
00:13:38,791 --> 00:13:40,666
[door opens and closes]

309
00:13:40,750 --> 00:13:44,583
- It feels like she's pushing
herself too hard.

310
00:13:44,666 --> 00:13:47,125
[piano keys clunking]
- That isn't how it goes!

311
00:13:47,208 --> 00:13:49,125
- I'm sorry!
- It's fine.

312
00:13:49,208 --> 00:13:50,875
Just take a breath
and play it through.

313
00:13:50,958 --> 00:13:53,958
- Focus, dummy, focus.
You've got this.

314
00:13:54,041 --> 00:13:56,041
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

315
00:13:56,125 --> 00:14:01,208
♪♪

316
00:14:01,291 --> 00:14:02,500
<i>- Good luck, Nagi!</i>

317
00:14:02,583 --> 00:14:04,333
<i>We'll be there cheering</i>
<i>you on!</i>

318
00:14:04,416 --> 00:14:07,291
<i>- You're the main draw</i>
<i>this year.</i>

319
00:14:07,375 --> 00:14:09,833
<i>- They say Mr. Ibata</i>
<i>will be attending.</i>

320
00:14:09,916 --> 00:14:11,125
<i>That means you have</i>
<i>to be perfect.</i>

321
00:14:11,208 --> 00:14:13,750
<i>Pass muster with him</i>
<i>and you're on your way.</i>

322
00:14:13,833 --> 00:14:15,708
<i>- I hear they're sending</i>
<i>out a reporter.</i>

323
00:14:15,791 --> 00:14:17,250
<i>Nagi's gonna get</i>
<i>a whole article written</i>

324
00:14:17,333 --> 00:14:19,958
<i>just about her.</i>

325
00:14:20,041 --> 00:14:24,291
♪♪

326
00:14:24,375 --> 00:14:27,291
- [crying]

327
00:14:27,375 --> 00:14:37,208
♪♪

328
00:14:38,625 --> 00:14:39,541
- Four days to go.

329
00:14:39,625 --> 00:14:42,916
I'm looking forward to this.

330
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:44,375
<i>- That's all that's left?</i>

331
00:14:44,458 --> 00:14:48,375
<i>I only have four more days</i>
<i>to make this piece my own.</i>

332
00:14:48,458 --> 00:14:49,958
<i>- We're all with you.</i>

333
00:14:50,041 --> 00:14:52,750
<i>- Would they care</i>
<i>if she wasn't cute?</i>

334
00:14:52,833 --> 00:14:55,041
<i>- They'll probably run her</i>
<i>photo in that magazine, too.</i>

335
00:14:55,125 --> 00:14:56,375
<i>- She's gonna own us.</i>

336
00:14:56,458 --> 00:14:57,541
<i>- Loli it up more,</i>
<i>princess.</i>

337
00:14:57,625 --> 00:14:58,208
<i>- Your parents must be</i>
<i>so proud of you.</i>

338
00:14:58,291 --> 00:14:59,583
<i>- Good luck!</i>

339
00:14:59,666 --> 00:15:02,541
<i>- Nothing but a pretty face.</i>

340
00:15:02,625 --> 00:15:04,333
<i>- This is torture,</i>

341
00:15:04,416 --> 00:15:06,291
<i>and I have to endure it</i>
<i>four more days.</i>

342
00:15:06,375 --> 00:15:13,708
♪♪

343
00:15:13,791 --> 00:15:15,125
- Mm?

344
00:15:15,208 --> 00:15:17,875
Ah, hey, Nagi!
[door closes]

345
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:19,708
[sighs]

346
00:15:19,791 --> 00:15:26,000
♪♪

347
00:15:26,083 --> 00:15:28,833
<i>- Help me, Mom.</i>
<i>I can't hear--</i>

348
00:15:28,916 --> 00:15:31,791
<i>I can't hear the notes!</i>

349
00:15:31,875 --> 00:15:35,083
<i>- Two years later</i>
<i>and here I am again,</i>

350
00:15:35,166 --> 00:15:37,375
<i>watching a kid melt down</i>
<i>in front of me.</i>

351
00:15:37,458 --> 00:15:41,541
♪♪

352
00:15:41,625 --> 00:15:43,500
What's up?

353
00:15:43,583 --> 00:15:46,958
- I'm so afraid,

354
00:15:47,041 --> 00:15:48,750
even though it's just
for school.

355
00:15:48,833 --> 00:15:51,083
It's not a competition
or anything,

356
00:15:51,166 --> 00:15:52,458
so why?

357
00:15:52,541 --> 00:15:55,083
- Welcome to the club, then.

358
00:15:55,166 --> 00:15:58,916
We're all afraid,
even me and Kousei.

359
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:03,291
Heck, I betcha even
Takeshi Aiza feels it.

360
00:16:03,375 --> 00:16:04,958
For those couple of minutes
out on stage,

361
00:16:05,041 --> 00:16:08,166
it feels like your whole
damn life's on the line.

362
00:16:08,250 --> 00:16:10,125
Scary as hell.

363
00:16:10,208 --> 00:16:11,916
Always will be.

364
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:15,625
- So how come you do it,
Ms. Seto?

365
00:16:15,708 --> 00:16:18,875
Why do you still put
yourself through that?

366
00:16:18,958 --> 00:16:20,250
- 'Cause once you're done,

367
00:16:20,333 --> 00:16:21,958
you can't imagine life
without it.

368
00:16:22,041 --> 00:16:25,625
All the pain and the fear
just melt away,

369
00:16:25,708 --> 00:16:27,791
and you're left with
something beautiful.

370
00:16:27,875 --> 00:16:30,125
Something you brought to life,
Nagi.

371
00:16:30,208 --> 00:16:33,833
<i>- When you've given them</i>
<i>a window into your soul,</i>

372
00:16:33,916 --> 00:16:35,291
<i>and your hearts beat as one,</i>

373
00:16:35,375 --> 00:16:38,625
<i>that's the moment when music</i>
<i>goes deeper than words.</i>

374
00:16:38,708 --> 00:16:40,833
- Maybe we're idiots,

375
00:16:40,916 --> 00:16:43,166
all of us chasing
that magic moment,

376
00:16:43,250 --> 00:16:47,333
willing to brave whatever peril
to taste that high.

377
00:16:47,416 --> 00:16:50,041
<i>It's a little</i>
<i>like being in love.</i>

378
00:16:50,125 --> 00:16:51,833
- It is magical, huh?

379
00:16:51,916 --> 00:16:53,166
- Got you, you little booger!

380
00:16:53,250 --> 00:16:55,625
Don't go hogging all
the bathroom!

381
00:16:55,708 --> 00:16:58,000
Hold onto that leg
for dear life, Koharu!

382
00:16:58,083 --> 00:17:02,416
I know why you wanna stay
in here forever, okay?

383
00:17:02,500 --> 00:17:04,083
You're afraid to walk out
on that stage

384
00:17:04,166 --> 00:17:07,833
because you practiced
your little heart out.

385
00:17:07,916 --> 00:17:09,375
You gave yourself,
body and soul,

386
00:17:09,458 --> 00:17:11,833
to the piano.

387
00:17:11,916 --> 00:17:14,416
Now you're afraid that maybe
it wasn't enough.

388
00:17:14,500 --> 00:17:16,208
Just know this.

389
00:17:16,291 --> 00:17:20,333
If anyone gives you the least
bit of grief at the festival,

390
00:17:20,416 --> 00:17:22,500
I'll kick their ass into space.

391
00:17:22,583 --> 00:17:24,250
So puff out that tiny chest.

392
00:17:24,333 --> 00:17:25,875
Remember, you're Kousei
Arima's apprentice!

393
00:17:25,958 --> 00:17:28,500
- [gasps]
I'm not his apprentice!

394
00:17:28,583 --> 00:17:30,041
I'm his mortal enemy!

395
00:17:30,125 --> 00:17:31,500
- That's the spirit.

396
00:17:31,583 --> 00:17:32,541
<i>Once you've taken the stage,</i>

397
00:17:32,625 --> 00:17:34,875
<i>you can duke it out.</i>

398
00:17:34,958 --> 00:17:41,166
♪♪

399
00:17:46,625 --> 00:17:49,250
- Watari?
- Yeah?

400
00:17:49,333 --> 00:17:50,875
- I need a favor.

401
00:17:50,958 --> 00:17:52,250
- Sure thing.

402
00:17:52,333 --> 00:17:53,750
- But you don't even know
what it is yet.

403
00:17:53,833 --> 00:17:54,458
- Long as you're
the one asking,

404
00:17:54,541 --> 00:17:57,208
it's cool.

405
00:17:57,291 --> 00:17:58,416
[chuckles]

406
00:17:58,500 --> 00:18:01,625
[indistinct chatter]

407
00:18:03,041 --> 00:18:04,875
[laughing]

408
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:07,375
I can't believe how many
cute girls they have here!

409
00:18:07,458 --> 00:18:09,250
This festival's
a ten out of ten!

410
00:18:09,333 --> 00:18:10,750
It's perfect!

411
00:18:10,833 --> 00:18:13,000
- Why do I feel like we should
have Watari on a leash?

412
00:18:13,083 --> 00:18:16,125
- Hmm?
Cool, there's a sign.

413
00:18:16,208 --> 00:18:18,666
Looks like it's
already started.

414
00:18:18,750 --> 00:18:21,708
[quirky music]

415
00:18:21,791 --> 00:18:23,958
♪♪

416
00:18:24,041 --> 00:18:25,791
- They should have picked
a shorter song.

417
00:18:25,875 --> 00:18:26,958
This is torture.

418
00:18:27,041 --> 00:18:28,166
- Hey, at least their
outfits are cute.

419
00:18:28,250 --> 00:18:30,666
Nagi's turn is coming up soon.
Am I right?

420
00:18:30,750 --> 00:18:33,041
How'd her song turn out?

421
00:18:33,125 --> 00:18:34,500
- Dunno.

422
00:18:34,583 --> 00:18:36,208
I asked her about it
but she refused

423
00:18:36,291 --> 00:18:37,625
to tell me anything.

424
00:18:37,708 --> 00:18:40,000
- So she's out
of that hero worship phase.

425
00:18:40,083 --> 00:18:41,416
[giggles]

426
00:18:41,500 --> 00:18:42,750
And how does big brother feel
about that?

427
00:18:42,833 --> 00:18:45,250
- No complaints here.

428
00:18:45,333 --> 00:18:46,666
- Good job, Komugi.

429
00:18:46,750 --> 00:18:48,166
- [sighs]

430
00:18:48,250 --> 00:18:50,416
I think that our number
went pretty well overall.

431
00:18:50,500 --> 00:18:52,333
Hold on.
Where's Nagi?

432
00:18:52,416 --> 00:18:56,125
- [groans]

433
00:18:56,208 --> 00:18:57,875
<i>We're following that?</i>

434
00:18:57,958 --> 00:18:59,666
- Look at you lazy kids!

435
00:18:59,750 --> 00:19:00,958
[crowd laughing]

436
00:19:01,041 --> 00:19:02,500
<i>- They're cracking up!</i>

437
00:19:02,583 --> 00:19:04,958
<i>Our waltz is so gonna kill</i>
<i>the mood!</i>

438
00:19:05,041 --> 00:19:05,958
- All in one place!
Wait, does that make--

439
00:19:06,041 --> 00:19:08,458
<i>- I didn't sign up for this!</i>

440
00:19:08,541 --> 00:19:10,291
- [humming]
- [grunts]

441
00:19:10,375 --> 00:19:13,333
- [humming]

442
00:19:16,291 --> 00:19:17,250
- How are you holding up?

443
00:19:17,333 --> 00:19:19,625
- I'm fine!
Cool as a cucumber!

444
00:19:19,708 --> 00:19:21,125
But why wouldn't I be?
Am I right?

445
00:19:21,208 --> 00:19:22,458
So how are you?

446
00:19:22,541 --> 00:19:24,291
If you're nervous,
I'm not seeing it.

447
00:19:24,375 --> 00:19:26,083
<i>Why is he so calm?</i>

448
00:19:26,166 --> 00:19:28,833
- Between the cute mascot suits
and the knife-wielding demon

449
00:19:28,916 --> 00:19:31,666
right before us, I--
[grunts]

450
00:19:34,041 --> 00:19:35,791
<i>That's right.</i>

451
00:19:35,875 --> 00:19:39,083
<i>The day we met,</i>
<i>her hand was trembling, too.</i>

452
00:19:42,833 --> 00:19:44,166
- [gasps]

453
00:19:44,250 --> 00:19:44,833
What do you think you're doing,
you pervert?

454
00:19:44,916 --> 00:19:46,125
Let go of my hand!

455
00:19:46,208 --> 00:19:48,833
- If you squeeze
your hand so hard,

456
00:19:48,916 --> 00:19:50,708
your fingers are gonna lock up.

457
00:19:50,791 --> 00:19:54,541
Now open it and just relax.

458
00:19:56,083 --> 00:19:57,333
- [gasps]

459
00:19:57,416 --> 00:19:58,916
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

460
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:02,041
<i>- Welcome to the club, then.</i>

461
00:20:02,125 --> 00:20:05,166
<i>We're all afraid,</i>
<i>even me and Kousei.</i>

462
00:20:06,416 --> 00:20:11,458
<i>- We're both here</i>
<i>because we have to be.</i>

463
00:20:11,541 --> 00:20:14,083
<i>Are you afraid, too?</i>

464
00:20:14,166 --> 00:20:17,625
<i>The same way I am?</i>

465
00:20:17,708 --> 00:20:19,625
- A friend of mine
told me something.

466
00:20:19,708 --> 00:20:22,500
Play with sincerity.

467
00:20:22,583 --> 00:20:24,000
Give the performance
of your life

468
00:20:24,083 --> 00:20:27,125
with everything
that you've got.

469
00:20:27,208 --> 00:20:29,958
- I'll try,
but I'm only 13 years old.

470
00:20:30,041 --> 00:20:32,041
What if my life's not enough?

471
00:20:32,125 --> 00:20:34,458
- Nagi, it's not
about the number.

472
00:20:34,541 --> 00:20:37,416
<i>For you and everyone</i>
<i>who's important to you,</i>

473
00:20:37,500 --> 00:20:40,208
those years are
a precious thing.

474
00:20:40,291 --> 00:20:44,625
Believe in yourself
and in your music.

475
00:20:44,708 --> 00:20:46,625
- [grunts]

476
00:20:48,250 --> 00:20:49,041
- All right, number eight.

477
00:20:49,125 --> 00:20:51,583
Time for you
to take the stage.

478
00:20:51,666 --> 00:20:55,291
- Well, that's us.

479
00:20:55,375 --> 00:20:56,666
- All right, you ready?

480
00:20:56,750 --> 00:20:57,583
- Uh-huh!

481
00:20:57,666 --> 00:21:00,708
[applause]

